    <text id="F8552T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Reverend T. P. <unclear>Bucher</unclear> sends his best wishes to Edward
                    McPherson during his term as a Congressman and encourages him to remember God
                    while serving his nation.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Honorable">Hon.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Edward">Edw.</abbr> McPherson, <abbr expan="Member of Congress"
                            >M. C.</abbr><lb/>Washington, D.C.</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1859-12-05"><abbr expan="December">Dec</abbr> 5. 59.</date>
                        <name type="place">Gettysburg,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir:</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>As I was not in town on the morning of your departure for Washington City, (and I
                    feel a just pride, as a Citizen of your <orig reg="hometown">home-town</orig>,
                    that it is honored with a Representative in the Halls of <abbr expan="National"
                        >Nat.</abbr> Legislation.) by this means, <hi rend="underline">I express my
                        regards for your personal welfare</hi>, adding the pleasure I would realize
                    in hearing of your distinguished mention among your <unclear>compears</unclear>
                    in the Congress of the U. S. Our acquaintance has not yet assumed the form of
                    personal friendship, nevertheless, as a Minister of the Gospel, my heart says
                    unto me, "wish him well, let your prayers, and benedictions be for him &amp;
                    upon him <add hand="h1" place="inline">whilst</add> in that Metropolis of
                    Government, and of sudden violence, and immorality, the Capitol of our Country."
                    Don't forget your God, in your devotion to your Country!</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>With great Respect, I am Yours <del rend="none" hand="h1"/></salute>
                    <signed>T. P. <unclear>Bucher</unclear></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
